<TITLE> Inter-district bus fares stay same </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 2 (bdnews24.com)  The government has decided to keep unchanged the fares of inter-district and long-distance buses including in Dhaka and Chittagong, a communication ministry statement said on Sunday. The statement was issued amid speculations that the bus fares would be cut after the government announced that the fare of bus and minibus run by diesel would come down by Tk 0.7 per kilometre following a cut in fuel prices on Oct 26. The statement said the fares of bus and minibus run by CNG in Dhaka and Chittagong and the surrounding districts had remained the same. The fare of inter-district and long-distance buses has been cut by Tk 0.7 per kilometre as the price of diesel came down by Tk 7 to Tk 48 from Tk 55. AFM Aminul Islam, the information officer at the communications ministry, told bdnews24.com on Sunday that there were a few diesel-run buses in Dhaka and that most of the buses were turned into CNG. "The diesel-run buses will also be converted to CNG-run ones in the next two months," he said. b
